  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "FPE in paddle.argmin and paddle.argmax\u00a0in PaddlePaddle before 2.6.0. This flaw can cause a runtime crash and a denial of service.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: The CVE concerns a software vulnerability in PaddlePaddle (an ML framework). It affects AI/ML software stacks and can cause denial of service via runtime crashes, impacting general-purpose AI systems. It uses standard CVE references (NVD, vendor advisory) as evidence. This fits the AI supply-chain software vulnerability scope."
